<title type="html"><![CDATA[Choosing between two mirroiting modes]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=101&amp;p=3959#p3959"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Roth wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Now, I noticed that the nametable at $2000 and $2800 (like in Membler's post on the other thread), as well as $2400 and $2C00(?) are the exact same.  Why is this?<br /></div><br /><br />It's because the NES has only enough VRAM for 2 nametables, but there's enough address space for 4.  They made it so you can select on the cartridge which 2 tables are usable (and which 2 tables are mirrored) by connecting a couple pins together on the cart.<br /><br />It's pretty much there so you can choose between scrolling horizontally or vertically without having partially-drawn parts of the nametable on-screen.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sat Aug 20, 2005 8:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
