Well, I don't understand why you're still asking questions so. Yeah, the vertical and horizontal mirroring means that the duplicating of the nametables themselves are done vertically or horizontally, respectively. It would seems more logical to call them on the opposite way, like on the solver pads where there is hardwired mirroring.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Aug 20, 2005 1:17 pm</p><hr />
